lead_paragraph: A big rig lost control on a rain-slicked highway Wednesday and hit a logging truck and a car in a fiery head-on crash that killed seven people. The accident just south of Dunsmuir shut down 60 miles of Interstate 5 for several hours, snarling Thanksgiving eve traffic. Dunsmuir is 300 miles north of San Francisco.
